{
  "stem": "6052.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On-- we are not eating and drinking for days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were cursed by the people we passed-- as children!",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember the curses they put on us, like, Juden schwein, and all this, which is like, pigs-- Jewish pigs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were-- we were kind of accommodated the farm before we could cross the border.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the border, we were accompanied by an adult, apparently also a paid assistant or paid helper, who should help us to go illegally into Yugoslavia and to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had papers by the Nazi authorities, with the Nazi stamps-- who we are and what we are and when we are born.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember the J stamp, which shows Jew, just in case somebody doubts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this was an-- also a requirement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Any Jewish person must have stamped in any document the Jew-- the J stamp, which showed Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And any man who did not have a Jewish name must have an addition of Moshe, I believe it was, and the woman had to have an addition of Sarah.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it did not apply to my mother, because she was called [NON-ENGLISH], so this was a Jewish name by itself.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also not to my father, who would not need it, because he was in Dachau, but was also called Chaim [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our group, there were no girls.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And here I have some kind of problem with myself, because at a later point, when my mother wrote me-- and I have letters here, or rather postcards here-- she asked-- and there was a group forming of-- of girls.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If she-- when she asked if girls-- if my sister should come also, we thought it too dangerous.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
